SYNOPSIS
    ce.pl {options} ce_model [ data_dir ]

DESCRIPTION
    Compute confidence estimation, using the given ce_model. All input files
    (i.e. files containing data from which CE model feature values are
    computed, e.g. q.tok, P.tok, p.score, etc.) are assumed to exist in the
    data_dir directory, or the current directory if data_dir is not
    specified. Output is written in a file called pr.ce within that
    directory, unless option "-output" is specified.

OPTIONS
    -output=O
     Output file name [data_dir/pr.ce]

    -path=P
     Colon-separated search path for feature-specific file arguments.
     Default is to search for files relative to data_dir first, then
     relative to directory where ce_model resides.

    -stats
     Write prediction accuracy statistics to STDERR; this assumes the
     presence in data_dir of reference translations for the source text
     (file r.tok).

    -verbose
     Be verbose

    -debug
     Produce debugging info

    -help, -h
     Print this message and exit

    -help=desc, -help=features, -help=depend
     Print additional help information: desc: model description files;
     features: confidence estimation features; depend: feature dependencies.

    -H
     Print all additional help information available.

